                    <h1 class="domdom">12</h1>

                    <h1>Film: <a href="/on/film/1667">Lot In Sodom (1933) Noizechoir (Live) &amp; The Fall Of The House Of Usher (1928) Phallictite (Live) @ The Cumberland Arms</a></h1>

                    <h2>12 Mar 2017, 7:30 p.m.</h2>

                    <p>Innovative American directors James Sibley Watson (a doctor who developed a 3D X-Ray film technique) and Melville Webber made two avant-garde films, the successful short horror The Fall Of The House Of Usher and the visually spectacular biblical tale of Lot In Sodom, tonight we present them scored live by NoizeChoir (Newcastle's premiere garglers) and Phallictite (Music's lowest ebb)
</p>

